---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy">
	<article class="policy">
		<header class="policy-header">
			<p class="policy-kicker">Legal</p>
			<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
			<p class="policy-intro">
				This Privacy Policy explains how Health Hearty (&quot;we&quot;, &quot;us&quot;, or
				&quot;our&quot;) collects, uses, and protects your information when you visit
				<code>healthhearty.com</code> (the &quot;Site&quot;).
			</p>
			<p class="policy-meta">Last updated: February 26, 2026</p>
		</header>

		<section>
			<h2>1. Who we are</h2>
			<p>
				Health Hearty is an informational website that publishes health and wellness content in
				plain language for educational purposes. The Site is accessible at
				<code>https://healthhearty.com</code>.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>2. Information we collect</h2>
			<p>
				We design Health Hearty to collect as little personal information as reasonably possible.
				Depending on how you interact with the Site, we may collect:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<strong>Usage data</strong>: Such as your IP address, browser type, operating system,
					referring URLs, pages viewed, and the dates and times of your visits. This information is
					typically collected automatically by our hosting and analytics providers.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Device and browser information</strong>: Technical information that helps us ensure
					the Site works correctly on your device (for example, screen size, language preferences,
					and basic browser configuration).
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Contact information (if you choose to share it)</strong>: If you contact us by
					email or via a contact form, we may store your name, email address, and the contents of
					your message so that we can respond.
				</li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>3. Cookies and similar technologies</h2>
			<p>
				We may use cookies and similar technologies to improve the Site and understand how it is
				used. Cookies are small text files stored on your device.
			</p>
			<p>We may use the following types of cookies:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<strong>Essential cookies</strong>: Necessary for the Site to function properly (for
					example, to keep basic security features working).
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Analytics cookies</strong>: Help us understand how visitors use the Site so we can
					improve content and usability.
				</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				You can usually configure your browser to refuse cookies or to alert you when cookies are
				being sent. However, some parts of the Site may not function properly without cookies.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>4. How we use your information</h2>
			<p>We may use the information described above to:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Operate, maintain, and improve the Site and its content.</li>
				<li>Monitor the performance and stability of the Site.</li>
				<li>Understand aggregate usage patterns and trends.</li>
				<li>Respond to questions or requests that you submit to us.</li>
				<li>Detect, prevent, or investigate security incidents or abuse.</li>
				<li>Comply with applicable laws, regulations, and legal processes.</li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>5. Legal bases for processing (EEA/UK visitors)</h2>
			<p>
				If you access the Site from the European Economic Area (EEA) or the United Kingdom (UK), our
				legal bases for processing your personal data may include:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<strong>Legitimate interests</strong> – for example, to maintain and secure the Site,
					understand usage patterns, and improve our content.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Compliance with legal obligations</strong> – to the extent we are required to
					retain or disclose information under applicable law.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Consent</strong> – where we rely on your consent (for example, for certain
					non-essential cookies or analytics), you may withdraw it at any time by adjusting your
					settings or contacting us.
				</li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>6. How we share information</h2>
			<p>
				We do not sell your personal information. We may share limited information with third
				parties in the following situations:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<strong>Service providers</strong>: We may share information with trusted service providers
					that help us operate or improve the Site (for example, hosting, security, or analytics
					services). These providers may only use your information as necessary to provide services
					to us and are required to protect it appropriately.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Legal requirements</strong>: We may disclose information if we believe in good
					faith that the disclosure is required by law, regulation, legal process, or governmental
					request, or to protect our rights, users, or the public.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Business transfers</strong>: If we are involved in a merger, acquisition, or sale
					of assets, your information may be transferred as part of that transaction, subject to
					appropriate confidentiality protections.
				</li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>7. International transfers</h2>
			<p>
				Our Site may be hosted and processed in countries other than the one where you reside. As a
				result, your information may be transferred to and stored on servers located in jurisdictions
				that may have different data protection laws than your home country.
			</p>
			<p>
				Where required by law, we take steps to ensure that appropriate safeguards are in place to
				protect your information when it is transferred internationally.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>8. Data retention</h2>
			<p>
				We retain information only for as long as is reasonably necessary to fulfill the purposes
				described in this Policy, unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law
				(for example, for legal, tax, or accounting reasons).
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>9. Your rights</h2>
			<p>
				Depending on where you live, you may have certain rights regarding your personal information,
				which can include:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Access</strong> – to request a copy of the personal data we hold about you.</li>
				<li><strong>Correction</strong> – to ask us to correct inaccurate or incomplete data.</li>
				<li><strong>Deletion</strong> – to request that we delete your personal data in certain cases.</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Restriction</strong> – to request that we limit how we process your information in
					certain circumstances.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Objection</strong> – to object to certain types of processing, including where we
					rely on legitimate interests.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Data portability</strong> – to request a copy of your data in a structured,
					commonly used, and machine-readable format where technically feasible.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Withdraw consent</strong> – where we rely on consent, you may withdraw it at any
					time without affecting the lawfulness of processing based on consent before its withdrawal.
				</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				To exercise any of these rights (or to ask a question about your rights), please contact us
				using the details in the &quot;How to contact us&quot; section below. We may need to verify
				your identity before responding to certain requests.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>10. Children’s privacy</h2>
			<p>
				Health Hearty is intended for a general audience and is not directed to children under the age
				of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe
				that a child has provided us with personal information without appropriate consent, please
				contact us and we will take reasonable steps to delete such information.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>11. Third-party links and content</h2>
			<p>
				The Site may contain links to third-party websites, services, or content (including external
				resources, reference materials, or images from providers such as Unsplash). We are not
				responsible for the privacy practices or the content of those third parties.
			</p>
			<p>
				We encourage you to review the privacy policies of any third-party sites or services you
				access through links on Health Hearty.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>12. Security</h2>
			<p>
				We use reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect the information we collect
				and store. However, no method of transmission over the internet or method of electronic
				storage is completely secure. We cannot guarantee absolute security of your information.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>13. Medical disclaimer</h2>
			<p>
				Health Hearty provides general health and wellness information for educational purposes only.
				Nothing on the Site is intended to be, or should be taken as, medical advice, diagnosis, or
				treatment. Always consult a qualified health professional with any questions about a medical
				condition, treatment, or before starting any new health regimen.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>14. Changes to this Privacy Policy</h2>
			<p>
				We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices,
				technologies, legal requirements, or for other operational reasons. When we make material
				changes, we will update the &quot;Last updated&quot; date at the top of this Policy. Your
				continued use of the Site after any changes become effective will signify that you have read
				and understood the updated Policy.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>15. How to contact us</h2>
			<p>
				If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, you can
				contact us at:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Website</strong>: <code>https://healthhearty.com</code></li>
				<li><strong>Email</strong>: <a href="mailto:privacy@healthhearty.com">privacy@healthhearty.com</a></li>
			</ul>
		</section>
	</article>
</Layout>

<style>
	.policy {
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto 3rem;
	}

	.policy-header {
		margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
	}

	.policy-kicker {
		margin: 0 0 0.4rem;
		font-size: 0.8rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.16em;
		color: #059669;
	}

	.policy-header h1 {
		margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
		font-size: clamp(2rem, 2.4vw + 1.2rem, 2.6rem);
		letter-spacing: -0.04em;
	}

	.policy-intro {
		margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
		color: #4b5563;
	}

	.policy-meta {
		margin: 0;
		font-size: 0.85rem;
		color: #6b7280;
	}

	section {
		margin-top: 1.75rem;
	}

	h2 {
		margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
		font-size: 1.15rem;
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
	}

	p {
		margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
		color: #111827;
	}

	ul {
		padding-left: 1.2rem;
		margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
	}

	li + li {
		margin-top: 0.3rem;
	}

	code {
		font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, 'Liberation Mono', 'Courier New',
			monospace;
		background-color: #f3f4f6;
		padding: 0.08rem 0.3rem;
		border-radius: 4px;
		font-size: 0.9em;
	}

	a {
		color: #047857;
		text-decoration: underline;
		text-underline-offset: 2px;
	}

	@media (max-width: 640px) {
		.policy {
			margin-bottom: 2.25rem;
		}
	}
</style>

